url = "http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/B9780123747129000158",
author = "Suresh C. Babu and Prabuddha Sanyal",
abstract = "Publisher Summary In this chapter, the basic elements of linear programming are introduced as it is applied to solve the diet/nutrition problem. It is a powerful tool for analyzing the cost of a nutritionally adequate ration prepared from different locally available foods. The sensitivity of linear programming to selected constraints is its major weakness. The food consumption constraints should be derived from the food consumption data collected in the community of interest. This chapter reviews some of the recent case studies that used the linear programming approach for achieving an optimal diet. It further illustrates the principles of the linear programming model along with its underlying assumptions and demonstrates the use of the Excel solver to determine the least expensive food combination that respects multiple nutritional constraints. The method shows how modern computer applications can be used to answer very practical questions. "
}
@incollection{Babu200939,
